  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the broiler to high and line a baking sheet with foil.",
    "In a small bowl whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, paprika, cumin, salt, and pepper to make a glaze.",
    "Thread the courgette rounds, bell pepper pieces, and onion wedges onto skewers, alternating colors for a vibrant look.",
    "Brush each skewer generously with the glaze, making sure all sides are coated.",
    "Place the skewers on the prepared baking sheet and broil for 4\u20135\u202fminutes, turning halfway through, until the vegetables are tender and slightly charred.",
    "Remove from the broiler and let sit for 2\u202fminutes before serving.",
    "Serve warm or at room temperature as a kid\u2011friendly snack or side.",
    "Enjoy the peppery crunch of these fresh, Argentinian-inspired skewers!"
